<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-07-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-07-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="862" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d862">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Leishman</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Prinkipo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-07-23"><hi rend="italic">July 23,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Leishman reports that the under secretary of state for foreign
                            affairs informed him by command of His Majesty that the Sultan would
                            receive Mr. Leishman immediately after the Selamnik ceremony next
                            Friday.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>